<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,872,1244]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
The presence of this species off the 
<collectingRegion box="[634,710,1156,1180]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Azores</collectingRegion>
needs further confirmation (
<bibRefCitation author="Santos R. S. &amp; Porteiro F. M. &amp; Barreiros J. P." box="[1020,1221,1156,1180]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 244" refId="ref43831" refString="Santos R. S., Porteiro F. M. &amp; Barreiros J. P. 1997. Marine fishes of the Azores: annotated checklist and bibliography. Arquipelago - Life and Marine Sciences. Suppl. 1: 1 - 244." type="journal article" year="1997">
Santos 
<emphasis box="[1101,1149,1156,1180]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al</emphasis>
. 1997
</bibRefCitation>
). The species 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire" baseAuthorityYear="1817" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Myliobatidae" genus="Rhinoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">R. marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is regarded as being present off southern mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[898,991,1188,1212]" name="Portugal" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, based on its geographical distribution (
<bibRefCitation author="Ebert D. A. &amp; Stehmann M. F. W." box="[249,514,1220,1244]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref39845" refString="Ebert D. A. &amp; Stehmann M. F. W. 2013. Sharks, batoids, and chimaeras of the North Atlantic. FAO Species Catalogue for Fishery Purposes no. 7, Food and Agriculture Organization, Rome." type="journal volume" year="2013">Ebert &amp; Stehmann 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
